Array: It's so dark here...
All part of the curse 'round here!
Headmaster Moraine calls it the "<color=bad>Night Shroud</color>." It's an old Fleshmancer curse preventing any light from reaching the island.
So even after you defeat the Dweller...
Aye, there ain't no fixin' that one. But hey, it's a living!
Speaking o' which, the <color=location>Town ov Lucent</color> oughtta be just ahead.
We'll be kicking it back at the local tavern. Can't leave 'til ye take care o' business, anyway.
Yolande, why even come here with us if you knew of the danger?
That's 'cause we be trusting the Captain, and it sure seems the Captain be trusting y'all.
If our adventure is to end here, I say so be it. We will have remained loyal to the end, and seen that much more of the world.
Right on, Keenathan!
Hey, y'all should come and see us at the inn, we'll be playing some music.
You're in a band?
Aye! Captain wants us to practice cheering up the places we visit.
Well, onwards then!
Valtraid's invitation sounds fun. How about we go to the inn and take it easy for a little while?
I don't know, we did arrive early, but...
Oh, don't feel bad! You've accomplished so much already.
Plus this cleansing thing, fighting a Dweller must be a pretty big deal.
Might as well be fully rested, don't you think?
Garl's right. We should wait for Moraine, and stay prepared.
Alright! Let's make for Lucent!
